						<summary>

						<p>Lintel of the main entrance into the same temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kulaśēkharadēva: Year 38, Āṉi = 1305-06 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records that a certain Kaḷattāvūruḍaiyāṉ Vīraṉ Kōlaṅkariyaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vēṇāvuḍaiyār of Kaḷattāvūr <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Oṉṉallākī[r]ttinallūr in Śevvirukkai-nāḍu caused the building of the <hi rend="italic">antarāḷa-maṉḍapa[m],</hi> where the images of Perumāḷ and Maṉṉār were placed, and which was to the east of the <hi rend="italic">atta(arddha)maṇḍapa,</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍapa</hi> with <hi rend="italic">sōpāna</hi> (steps), in front of the <hi rend="italic">antarāḷa-maṇḍapa,</hi> in the temple of the god Uttamaśōḻaviṇṇagara Āḻvār.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
